// AdminService — platform-admin (`is_system_admin=true`) management plane.
//
// Migrated from REST handlers in backend/internal/api/rest/v1/admin/* per
// .claude/plans/proto-naming-conventions.md. Covers the batch-1 surface:
//   * Dashboard           — system stats
//   * Users               — list/get/update/disable/enable/grant/revoke admin
//                           + verify/unverify email
//   * Organizations       — list/get/members/delete
//   * Runners             — list/get/disable/enable/delete (across all orgs)
//   * AuditLogs           — list with filters
//   * Relays              — list/get/stats/force-unregister
//   * SupportTickets      — list/get/stats/list-messages/status/assign/attachment-url
//                           (Reply with multipart attachments stays on REST)
//
// AdminAuthService — admin-console login flow.
//
// Mirrors backend/internal/api/rest/v1/admin/auth.go. The login RPC is
// PUBLIC (no auth interceptor) because the caller does not yet hold a
// bearer; the handler enforces is_system_admin + is_active server-side.
// GetMe lives on AdminAuthSessionService (auth-required).
//
// Auth model (conventions §3.5 EXCEPTION — platform-admin scoped):
//   Every RPC requires (1) a valid bearer JWT (standard auth interceptor)
//   AND (2) the calling user's `is_system_admin = true` AND `is_active =
//   true` flags. The Connect admin interceptor combines REST's
//   `AuthMiddleware` + `AdminMiddleware` (backend/internal/middleware/admin.go)
//   into a single pipeline step. Per conventions §3.5 exception #2, admin
//   request messages do NOT carry `org_slug` at tag 1; tenant is the whole
//   platform and is implied by the admin interceptor.
//
// Audit-log shape:
//   REST handlers call `LogAdminAction` from a `gin.Context` to read the
//   admin user ID + IP + user-agent. The Connect handler reads:
//     * admin user ID  — from the auth interceptor's TenantContext
//     * IP address     — from req.Peer().Addr (Connect's transport hook)
//     * user-agent     — from req.Header().Get("User-Agent")
//   so audit logging is parity-preserving across both transports.

